HEADWORD: Cavally
<hw>Ca*val"ly</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. Pg.
<ets>cavalla</ets> a kind of fish; Sp. <ets>caballa</ets>; prob. fr. Pg.
<ets>cavallo</ets> horse, Sp. <ets>caballa</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A carangoid fish of the Atlantic coast
(<spn>Caranx hippos</spn>): -- called also <altname>horse
crevall⟦eacute⟧</altname>. <note>[See <xex>Illust.</xex> under
<er>Carangoid</er>.]</note></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

